channel.title: Tay Pod
channel.description:
Taylor Negron is proud of being a native Angeleno and remembers when the palm trees were shorter and "Tomorrowland" was modern. His education was limited, he went to UCLA... for lunch. As a writer, Negron has enjoyed much success having written and starred in Gangster Planet, a four-character domestic comedy set during the Los Angeles riots. A "Critics Choice", The Los Angeles Times wrote, "If Aristophanes were alive today and had watched L.A. burn, Gangster Planet could be the result ... acute cynicism with a clown's humanism."
Taylor has just completed his new play Yoga Bitch - a scorching take on the current yoga trend. He is a regular contributor to Jill Solloways' “Sit and Spin” and Hilary Carlips' online magazine “Fresh Yarns”. Negron is also a columnist for the magazine Highway 111 where his new novel, Murder in La Quinta, is being serialized. He has appeared in over 100 film and television shows. An accomplished stand-up comedian, he has appeared in his own HBO special, appeared on The Tonight Show and performs regularly across the United States.

Now you can watch him daily in the new series TayPod on YakkYakk.com Taylor's nervous about podcasting, but he'll always have his daughter to remind him what's important in life: precocious celebrity misbehavior. But why does he have to be nice to Ryan Seacrest? - What good is an intern when he/she is a total transgendered airhead? Thank goodness Taylor's a real showbiz trooper...
